Vice President Pence met with Guatemalan President Jimmy Morales in Miami, Florida at the Conference on Prosperity and Security in Central America. Pence recognized Guatemala for its commitment to the Alliance for Prosperity and its support in fighting illegal drug trafficking. He emphasized the need to fight corruption and impunity, supporting the Attorney General and the UN Commission Against Impunity and Corruption. They discussed the crisis in Venezuela and expressed concern for the Venezuelan people. Pence and Morales reiterated their commitment to strengthening the bilateral relationship and advancing shared goals of security and prosperity.